                    <history>
                        <origin notBefore="1775" notAfter="1799" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
                            <p>Written in Iceland in the third quarter of the eighteenth century. In
                                the epilogue, dated <q xml:lang="is">á Núpi 1787</q>, <name type="person" key="MagMag009">Magnús Magnússon</name> informs
                                that the collection is transcribed for his father's brother <name type="person" key="JonBjo005">Jón Björnsson</name>, partly by
                                Jón's son <name type="person" key="BjoJon003">Björn</name>, partly -
                                after the death of Björn - by Magnús Magnússon himself.</p>
